CSS FLEXBOX : a layout system used to arrange elements in rows or columns easily and responsively. It helps align, space, and distribute items inside a container.
Flexbox is mainly used for one-dimensional layouts (row or column).
Basic Idea of Flexbox
Flexbox works with two parts:

Flex Container
Flex Items

Example:
            <div class="container">
              <div class="box">1</div>
              <div class="box">2</div>
              <div class="box">3</div>
            </div>
CSS:
              .container {
                display: flex;
              }
Now the boxes will align in a row automatically.

1️⃣ Flex Container
You create a flex container using:
display: flex;

Example:
              .container {
                display: flex;
              }
Now all children become flex items.

2️⃣ Flex Direction
Controls direction of items.
                    .container {
                      display: flex;
                      flex-direction: row;
                    }
Value                	Meaning
row	                left → right
row-reverse	        right → left
column	            top → bottom
column-reverse	    bottom → top

Example:
          .container {
            flex-direction: column;
          }
Items stack vertically.

3️⃣ Justify Content (Main Axis)
Controls horizontal alignment (in row layout).
                .container {
                  justify-content: center;
                }
Value              	Result
flex-start        	left
center            	center
flex-end          	right
space-between	      equal space between
space-around	      equal space around
space-evenly	      evenly spaced

Example:
              .container {
                justify-content: space-between;
              }
4️⃣ Align Items (Cross Axis)
Controls vertical alignment.
              .container {
                align-items: center;
              }

Value	                  Meaning
stretch	                default
center	             center vertically
flex-start	             top
flex-end	               bottom

Example:
                .container {
                  align-items: center;
                }
5️⃣ Gap (Space Between Items)
                .container {
                  gap: 20px;
                }
Adds space between flex items.
Complete Example
HTML:
            <div class="container">
              <div class="box">1</div>
              <div class="box">2</div>
              <div class="box">3</div>
            </div>

CSS:
              .container {
                display: flex;
                justify-content: center;
                align-items: center;
                gap: 20px;
              }
              .box {
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                background: lightblue;
              }

Result:
Boxes appear in a row
Centered horizontally and vertically
20px gap between them
------------------------------------------------------------------------

Flex Item Properties
These apply to individual items.

flex-grow
Allows item to grow and fill space.
                  .box {
                    flex-grow: 1;
                  }

flex-shrink
Controls shrinking when space is small.
              flex-shrink: 1;

flex-basis
            Sets initial size.
            flex-basis: 200px;


Quick Summary
Property	                    Purpose
display:flex	              creates flex container
flex-direction	            row or column
justify-content	            horizontal alignment
align-items	                vertical alignment
gap	                        space between items


Easy Way to Remember
Flexbox = alignment + spacing + responsive layout

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
These three Flexbox layouts appear on almost every modern website. Once you understand them, a lot of page layouts become much easier.

1️⃣ Centering Content (Perfect Center)
One of the most common uses of Flexbox is centering something horizontally and vertically.
HTML
          <div class="container">
            <div class="box">Centered Box</div>
          </div>
CSS
          .container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 300px;
          }
          
          .box {
            width: 120px;
            height: 120px;
            background: lightblue;
          }
Key properties
justify-content → horizontal center
align-items → vertical center

This is widely used for:
login forms
hero sections
modals

2️⃣ Navigation Bar Layout
Flexbox is perfect for horizontal menus and navigation bars.
HTML
              <nav class="navbar">
                <div class="logo">Logo</div>
                <ul class="menu">
                  <li>Home</li>
                  <li>About</li>
                  <li>Contact</li>
                </ul>
              </nav>
CSS
              .navbar {
                display: flex;
                justify-content: space-between;
                align-items: center;
              }
              
              .menu {
                display: flex;
                gap: 20px;
                list-style: none;
              }
What happens
Logo ← left
Menu items → right
Flexbox automatically spaces the items.

3️⃣ Card Grid Layout
Flexbox is often used for cards, product listings, and galleries.
HTML
            <div class="container">
              <div class="card">Card 1</div>
              <div class="card">Card 2</div>
              <div class="card">Card 3</div>
              <div class="card">Card 4</div>
            </div>
CSS
            .container {
              display: flex;
              flex-wrap: wrap;
              gap: 20px;
            }
            
            .card {
              width: 200px;
              height: 150px;
              background: lightgray;
            }
Key property
flex-wrap: wrap;
This allows cards to move to the next row automatically.

Quick Summary
Layout	                  Key Flexbox Properties
Center content	        justify-content, align-items
Navbar	                justify-content: space-between
Card grid	                  flex-wrap, gap

💡 Pro tip developers remember
Flexbox → 1-dimensional layouts
Grid → 2-dimensional layouts
Flexbox controls rows OR columns, while Grid controls both.
