CSS GridBox : 
1️⃣ What CSS Grid Is
CSS Grid is a layout system for creating complex web layouts using rows and columns.
You create:
a Grid Container (parent)
Grid Items (children inside the container)

Example:
.container {
  display: grid;
}
Now all direct children of .container become grid items.

2️⃣ Basic Grid Example
                <div class="container">
                  <div class="box">1</div>
                  <div class="box">2</div>
                  <div class="box">3</div>
                </div>
                  .container {
                    display: grid;
                    grid-template-columns: 200px 200px 200px;
                  }
Result:
[1] [2] [3]
You created 3 columns of 200px.

3️⃣ Grid Terminology
Important grid concepts:
Term	                        Meaning
Grid Container	          Parent with display:grid
Grid Item                	Children inside the grid
Grid Line	                The lines separating rows and columns
Grid Cell	                Single box in grid
Grid Track	                Row or column
Grid Area	                Multiple cells combined

Example visual:
|----|----|----|
| A  | B  | C  |
|----|----|----|
| D  | E  | F  |
|----|----|----|

4️⃣ Creating Columns
grid-template-columns
.container{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns: 100px 100px 100px;
}

Creates 3 columns.
Result:
[ ] [ ] [ ]

Using fr (fraction unit)
grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
Each column gets equal space.
Example:
| 1fr | 1fr | 1fr |

If container = 900px
300px | 300px | 300px

Example:
grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
Layout:
25% | 50% | 25%


5️⃣ Creating Rows
grid-template-rows: 100px 200px;
Creates 2 rows.
Example:
Row 1 → 100px
Row 2 → 200px

6️⃣ Grid Gap (Spacing)
Adds space between items.
gap: 20px;
or
row-gap: 10px;
column-gap: 20px;
Example:
[box]   [box]
     gap
[box]   [box]

7️⃣ Placing Items Using Grid Lines
Example grid:

1   2   3   4
|---|---|---|
| A | B | C |
|---|---|---|

You can place items using grid lines.
          .item {
            grid-column: 1 / 3;
          }

This means:
start at line 1
end at line 3

Item spans 2 columns.
Example:
grid-row: 1 / 3;
Spans 2 rows.

8️⃣ grid-column and grid-row
              .item {
                grid-column: 2 / 4;
                grid-row: 1 / 3;
              }
This means:
columns: 2 → 4
rows:    1 → 3
Item covers multiple cells.

9️⃣ repeat() Function
Instead of writing columns many times:
❌

grid-template-columns: 100px 100px 100px 100px;
✅

grid-template-columns: repeat(4,100px);
Example:
grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr);
Creates:
| 1fr | 1fr | 1fr |

🔟 Auto Grid
grid-auto-rows
grid-auto-rows: 100px;
All automatic rows will be 100px.
grid-auto-columns
grid-auto-columns: 200px;
............................................................................................................

11️⃣ Grid Template Areas (Very Powerful)
Allows visual layout design.
Example:
            .container{
             display:grid;
             grid-template-areas:
               "header header"
               "sidebar content"
               "footer footer";
            }
Assign areas:
            .header{ grid-area: header; }
            .sidebar{ grid-area: sidebar; }
            .content{ grid-area: content; }
            .footer{ grid-area: footer; }

Layout becomes:
HEADER HEADER
SIDEBAR CONTENT
FOOTER FOOTER
Very clean for website layouts.

12️⃣ Aligning Grid Items
Horizontal alignment    justify-items: center;
Vertical alignment      align-items: center;

Example:
          .container{
           display:grid;
           justify-items:center;
           align-items:center;
          }
Items appear centered in each cell.

13️⃣ Align Whole Grid
justify-content
align-content

Example:
justify-content:center;
align-content:center;
Moves entire grid inside container.

14️⃣ place-items (Shortcut)
Instead of writing:
align-items:center;
justify-items:center;
Use:
place-items:center;


15️⃣ Responsive Grid
Use auto-fit / auto-fill
Example:
grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px,1fr));

Meaning:
Minimum column = 200px
Maximum = 1fr
Automatically adjusts columns.
Used for responsive card layouts.

16️⃣ Example Real Website Layout
              .container{
               display:grid;
               grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
               grid-template-rows: 80px 1fr 60px;
               grid-template-areas:
                 "header header"
                 "sidebar content"
                 "footer footer";
              }

Layout:
HEADER    HEADER
SIDEBAR   CONTENT
FOOTER    FOOTER


17️⃣ Grid vs Flexbox
Feature	            Grid	          Flexbox
Direction	           2D	              1D
Layout	        Rows + Columns	  Row OR Column
Best for	        Page layout	    Components
Control	             High	          Medium

Example usage:
Grid → Page layout
Flexbox → Navbar / buttons

18️⃣ Most Important Grid Properties (Remember)
Container properties:
                    display: grid
                    grid-template-columns
                    grid-template-rows
                    gap
                    grid-template-areas
                    justify-items
                    align-items

Item properties:
                    grid-column
                    grid-row
                    grid-area
                    justify-self
                    align-self

19️⃣ Simple Grid Example
                  .container{
                   display:grid;
                   grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr);
                   gap:10px;
                  }

Result:
[box] [box] [box]
[box] [box] [box]

20️⃣ Why Developers Love Grid
Grid makes it easy to build:
dashboards
card layouts
galleries
website layouts
responsive pages
with very little code.












